Sugar in fruit juices, cakes, and biscuits may lead to your kid’s liver transplant. All thanks to this new disease called non-alcoholic fatty liver disease. Sugar is 50% glucose, and 50% fructose. Glucose gives energy. But fructose gets stored as fat in the liver. Your stomach cannot metabolize fructose so most of it happens in the liver. Fructose goes to the liver, and converts into liver fat, causing non-alcoholic fatty liver disease, the second stage being liver cirrhosis. Let's cut back on sugary drinks and treats. Garlic can be grown in pots, wine barrels, raised, beds, or in the ground. Do you want to grow garlic like the ones from the store? Try growing soft snack varieties. Soft neck varieties store longer than hard neck varieties, which is why I stores mainly sell soft neck garlic for the long lasting shelf life. Soft neck varieties store very well, lasting 9-12 months which makes soft neck, garlic butter for storage (soft neck varieties can be braided for storage after curing) Harden neck don’t last as long in storage, only 4-6 months-ish Save this post to come back to when you’re ready to get your garlic in the ground. #garden #backyardgarden #homestead #lifeouthere #growinggarlic #garlic #gardens
